<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFE76A58FDFC9D181C64B06C" box="[512,612,2881,2910]" name="Vietnam" pageId="28" pageNumber="786">Tonkin</collectingCountry>
Greater Bamboo Bat (7. tonkinensis) in Yunnan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFE76A58FF569D3D1C25B0E6" pageId="28" pageNumber="786" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFE76A58FF569D3D1C25B0E6" blockId="28.[168,1375,1814,3068]" pageId="28" pageNumber="786">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFE76A58FF569D3D1C09B0B7" bold="true" box="[170,521,2916,2949]" pageId="28" pageNumber="786">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFFE76A58FDEA9D3D1C4BB0B7" box="[534,587,2916,2949]" country="Cameroon" name="North" pageId="28" pageNumber="786">Not</collectingRegion>
assessed on The IUCN Red List. The Pygmy Bamboo Bat is currently known only from the type locality, although it may be found over a wider area than currently known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
